## 9. Interactive States

### Buttons

**Primary Button (Light Mode):**

- Default: `#4f67eb` background, white text
- Hover: `#3d52d4` background
- Active: Slightly darker with inset shadow
- Focus: Blue ring (3px, 20% opacity)
- Disabled: 50% opacity, no pointer events

**Outlined Button (Light Mode):**

- Default: Transparent background, `#e5e7eb` border
- Hover: `#eff1fc` background
- Active: Slightly darker background

**Dark Mode Adjustments:**

- Primary: `#7c90f2` background, dark text
- Outlined: `#2d3448` border, `#2a3250` hover

### Input Fields

**Light Mode:**

- Default: White background, `#e5e7eb` border
- Hover: Slightly darker border
- Focus: `#4f67eb` border, blue glow
- Disabled: Gray background, no interaction

**Dark Mode:**

- Default: `#1a1d2e` background, `#2d3448` border
- Focus: `#7c90f2` border, blue glow

### Cards

**Light Mode:**

- Default: White background, subtle shadow
- Hover: Larger shadow (lift effect)
- Active: Pressed state with subtle inset

**Dark Mode:**

- Default: `#1a1d2e` background, `#2d3448` border
- Hover: Lighter border, larger shadow

---

## 10. Responsive Breakpoints

### Mobile (< 768px)

- Single column layouts
- Stacked hero sections
- Hidden navigation links (menu icon instead)
- Full-width cards
- Smaller font sizes
- Reduced padding

### Tablet (768px - 1024px)

- 2-column grids for cards
- Maintained navigation
- Medium padding

### Desktop (> 1024px)

- 3-column grids for opportunity cards
- Full navigation visible
- Maximum content width: 1280px
- Optimal spacing and padding

---

## 11. Accessibility Features

### Color Contrast

- All text meets WCAG AA standards (4.5:1 for normal text)
- Interactive elements have 3:1 contrast minimum
- Focus states clearly visible

### Keyboard Navigation

- Tab order follows logical flow
- Focus indicators on all interactive elements
- Skip to main content link

### Screen Reader Support

- Semantic HTML elements
- ARIA labels on icon-only buttons
- Alt text on images
- Status announcements for dynamic content

---

## 12. Animation & Transitions

### Timing

- Fast: 150ms (hover states)
- Medium: 200ms (theme toggle, tab switches)
- Slow: 300ms (page transitions, modal animations)

### Easing

- Standard: `ease-in-out`
- Enter: `ease-out`
- Exit: `ease-in`

### Animated Elements

- Button hover states
- Card hover lift
- Theme toggle
- Tab switching
- Form validation feedback
- Loading states

---

This comprehensive design specification ensures consistency across all pages and modes of the AttachLink platform. All visual elements follow the blue color scheme in both light and dark modes, creating a cohesive and professional appearance.
